betterquesting:10.desc:8:
You'll need ingredients and therefore the matching tools. That's the way you start:

Craft a Wooden Knife and collect some bark. (hit the tree with the knife)


Your goal is the "Book of Herblore".

To process ingredients, you need a Mortar & Pestle.
The recipe can be found in your spell book.

To use the magic, find a Stonehenge in the world. It's usable during the night. (Full moon is required)

You can find the layout for every spell in the "Book of Herblore".

(Info: The Stonehenge contains some hard-to-see markings for the flowers)

A Shamans Hut is findable in the world but you only need the straw from the roof which is craftable.

Craft a §lShear§r, destroy some §n§3§2Grass§r§r and dry it in the furnace.

Finally, bundle it together.

Your Wand discharges slowly, so you'll need some ammo.

You can store your stuff in a "Pouch", which is very practical.

It can be filled with "Pedal". Check your book for what materials you should have with you.

To use the magic, you need the Staff from Roots 2.

But first, the "Imbuer" is required.

Place the Wand on the base and add some dust to it.
Then wait a bit until the wand is fully charged so can finally start with your magic.

Welcome in the age of Cowboys & Indians.

The "Totempedia" is the guide for this mod, craft it!

In every Indian Village is a totem pole, you need carving tools for it.

Place some logs at a good position and edit them with your tools.
A real Indian has a good Tipi, check the Manuel and complete it.
This Book contains all info about the mod.

The Totem Pole alone is not very useful (apart from the look).
With the right sound, atmosphere, dance & voice, you will receive your "present of the gods".

Try more dancing

How about the "Zaphkiel Waltz"?
With this dance you can enchant your Saplings to "Zeder Saplings".
You can improve your default §nFlute§r into a better one with "Serenade for Syrinx".
Shamans are Wizards, their spells are written in books.

In the Stonehenge you can also create §7Runestones§r, read in the "Book of Herblore" for how it works.

You will need this later, for your own incantation circle.
The last Book is in the row, the one with the secret magic in the magical circle.

In every incantation circle belongs a Campfire, a ceremonial Campfire.

How to make it? Look inside your book, its quick and easy.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Godfather spoke "I would be Light"
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Its cold and you are captured in the darkness, so, you need some coal.


For this you need:
- a few Logs
- 1 Flint & Steel
- a pit

Let's get started:

Dig a pit -> put some Log-Piles inside -> lock it with some Dirt or Stone (but ignite the last Log-Pile, before you close it completely)

Now wait about one in-game day and you can collect your Charcoal.

The Grinder.
An easy way for an efficient work flow.

Take a look into it, it can do a lot.

betterquesting:10.name:8: An upgrade for the smelting speed
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
We already have one type of efficient machine.

Now, we need to §4smelt§r the result of it.

§7§1§fPigs are cleanly animals and they love it to root in the dirt (to lose parasites of course).

Mud is the favourite ground for them, on this they feel good.
6 should be enough. (for the moment)

1 cow is silent, 2 cows are okay but more is loud.

But you need milk, so milking a cow is the goal.

Who came first ? The §nEgg§r or the §nChicken§r ?

Nevermind, simply start with a Nest and place some Seeds around.

And soon you will have some Chickens ... or other things with feathers. :/

Now milk is in your possession, so cheese is close. You need a Cheese Shape and a Milk Bucket.

To create cheese, fill the shape with the milk, other kinds of milk are possible, but they don't help to complete this quest.

Let the magic begin and voilà you have §eCheese§r.

A few basic rules for your animals.

1. they have to be happy!
To do this, you will need some troughs. (for food and water)

Pigs, Cows & Chickens are not alone.

Hamsters, Goats, Sheep & Rabbits and more enrich our world.

Every animal has there own food and requirements.

In case of emergency, have some food on stock. (for all of them)

After a mud party, pigs want something to eat. With some vegetables and milk you can produce pig - "food".

The bucket is your tool, just fill it in the trough.

When Pigs are happy and fed up, they search some truffles for you.

A delicious soup is made out of this.

If there are no truffles in the stable, take your pig with you to an journey.

If we have birds and a nest, we get some eggs in the near future.

Collect some and cook delicious Omelettes.

Now milk is in your possession, so cheese is close. You need a Cheese Shape and a Milk Bucket.

To create cheese, fill the shape with the milk, other kinds of milk are possible, but they don't help to complete this quest.

Let the magic begin and voilà you have §eCheese§r.

The other 2 blocks don't have any upgrades, so we just upgrade the Vanilla Furnace.

Build one of these and place it next to a furnace.
But don't forget: this block needs some electrical power.

Now you have the basic stuff for Filters.


Well, the next step is a Net, or more. Place the Filter 1 block deep under the water, between the Protruding Sticks you have to clamp your net.
There are 3 different sizes with 3 different durabilities.

Test out, which one is the best for you.
You can find no caves? Then this is a good start to collect some materials.

To sieve your stuff is to hard ? Or you're just to lazy? Then use the Waterstrainer mod!

It can find a lot in the water.

The Filter is universal, it can collect a lot of loot. And Fish, delicious fish. :)

But only with a bait!

Combine Bait and a Pot in a crafting table.

Together with a Net we can start the §7adventure§f.

The mod has a tool to check your efficiency-level.

Test it!
To cut your cheese, a good knife would be appropriate.
For the beginning, we need some materials. Collect some in the §8Nether§8§r, but be careful!

Let's start simple, collect some resources for seeds

Info: the required §nSeed§r is a §eT1 Seed.

Level 2 seeds are a bit more expensive, prepare yourself.
Craft an Infusion Crystal to upgrade your seeds.

Info: the required §nSeed§r is a § §aT2 Seed.
A magical furnace, faster, better, stronger, harder... oh, wrong topic.
Ridiculous speed!
The new furnace is good, but just "good" is not good enough. Upgrade it to level 3!
Be §3§9Sonic§r!
Speed of light is a joke!

The last level? Hmm, craft it and you will find out.

Info: the required §nSeed§r is a §4T5 Seed.

You are intelligent so you can calculate. Level 3 seeds are waiting for you.

Info: the required §nSeed§r is a §6T3 Seed.

Level 4 is needed for a lot of plants, so craft a good amount from them and get more resources.

Info: the required §nSeed§r is a §bT4 Seed.
This is the ultimate level, the mod has more stuff for you, look in JEI and find out what new items are available now.
No Description. <- This must be bug for sure!

Every registered mob can drop some chunks of their life.

These are rare and good for plants. :)

To improve the speed, craft 2 Pre-heaters and place one on each side.
Now connect them with power (on top, middle block) and you're done.
One item with many possible applications.

We start easy.

Celebrate the mod with some §cR§c§2G§1B§f balloons!

You can brew potions, its a strong magic.

Create a Cauldron first!
With the Cauldron alone, you can't brew, the ingredients must be prepared!

The Altar of light.

An interesting item, to grow §eGlowstone§r.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Desert Eagle ... or simply a gun.
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
A new weapon has appeared.

Construct a weapon and hunt with it for new materials.
To fill your potions, you need Vials/Bottles. Craft a good amount!

Relics.

Start simple and increase your learning curve.

Info: The §2Lilipad of Fertility§r lets your plants grow faster.

A additional Relic is the "Interdiction Torch".
This Torch repels mobs around it.

The pedestal is a universal item.

As an example:
Equiped with a sword, it can kill mobs around it.

Like the "Cloak of Invisibility" from Harry Potter, this cape hides you from mobs in the night.
You only need some Wool and magic ingredients to craft it.

Ammo is diverse:
- Default ammo
- Ammo with some effects

With the acquired dust, you should have all ingredients together to brew potions now.
Try 2 different types:
- Regeneration
- Absorption

betterquesting:10.name:8: Engineer's Manuel - The heart of IE
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The book of engineer's.

Inside this book, you can find the universe. (of IE)
A good engineer can work solo, but a God engineer uses tools.

To work further, Coal Coke is required.

Build order:

- Craft 27x Coke Bricks
- Place them in a 3x3x3 shape
- Right click the finished product with your Engineer's Hammer

You don't want to have your inventory full of stuff? 
Then the Engineer's Toolbox is the right item for you. It can hold Wires, Shears, Books, Tools and more.

To improve your existing Blast Furnace, dismantle it and cover the Blast Bricks with §7Steel§r.

Place again the 27x Bricks in a 3x3x3 shape, but now with a Hopper on top.

Configuration:
- on top is the input for Iron
- at the front is the output for §7Steel§r
- at the back is the output for Slag

To improve the speed, craft 2 Pre-heaters and place one at each side.
Now connect them with power (on top) and you're done.

Some recipes need §8§7Steel§r.

Use the Blast Furnace to create §8§7Steel§r.

(Iron + Charcoal or Coal Coke (via Coke Oven) = §7Steel§r)

A Crude Blast Furnace is your first step.

Build order:

- Craft 27x Blast Bricks
- Place them in a 3x3x3 shape
- Right click the finished product with your Engineer's Hammer

Alloys are also required sometimes, so you need the Alloy Kiln.

Build order:

- Craft 8x Kiln Bricks
- Place them in a 2x2x2 shape
- Right click the finished product with your Engineer's Hammer
Build the Engineer's Workbench, with it you can make a lot more stuff.

To get ahead, you need energy. (RF, IF, ...)
Many different possibilities are available:
- Waterwheels
- Windmills
- Thermoelectric Generator
- and more ...

Here you test the "Power of Water" via Waterwheels. So, craft the required components.

To install your Wheel, place the dynamo and in front of it, you place the Waterwheel.
Last step, take some Buckets of Water and place them above the Waterwheel.

To get ahead, you need energy. (RF, IF, ...)
Many different possibilities are available:
- Waterwheels
- Windmills
- Thermoelectric Generator
- and more ...

Here you test the "Power of Wind" via Windmills. So, craft the required components.

Windmills need a clear area, the best way is ta have a high place, with vision to the Sky.
To install the Windmill, place the dynamo and in front of it, the Windmill. After a short delay, it will start to turn.

Secret Info: To improve your efficiency, cover the Windmill with some "Windmill Sails".
(For each wing, 1 sail)

Previously installed in the machine and now you search for more applications.

Conveyor Belts are better pipes (at least optically). They can transport into machine inputs and out of machine outputs.

They can also be stopped with a Redstone-signal and they have multiple versions:
- Dropping Conveyor Belt
- Covered Conveyor Belt
- Vertical Conveyor Belt

The fast way to create Plates, Wires, Gears and more is the Metal Press.
This multi-block machine can be equipped with different Press Molds.

To enable the machine, a simple right click with the Engineer's Hammer is enough.

With Treated Wood your possibilities are almost limitless.

A Motor Boat as example can be filled with Gasoline for a great maximum speed.


Info: You need the Engineer's Workbench for it.

Projectors are the easy way, in case you don't know, how the shape of a machine.

You can combine a Projector with your Engineer's Manuel, to lock the machine blue-print.

Your already producing energy, but how can you move it?

With Cables and Connectors/Relays!
Several cables can be connected to one Relay, but only 1 Cable is collectable to 1 Connector.
You can change the voltage with Transformers.

Play a little bit with them.

Lubricant is good for every machine, they work better with it.

The Can is versatile, Golems will feel like new.

To store big amounts of Oil, or Coal, you can build:
- a Silo for Items
- a Tank for Liquids

Building requirements:
- 4 Treated Wood Fence
- 34 / 50 Iron Sheetmetal

34 Sheetmetal for the Tank and 50 for the Silo.

Treated Wood = any Wood + Creosote Oil -> voilà.

Creosote Oil is available from the Coke Oven.

More materials are needed.

Plates are made out of Ingots + Engineer's Hammer

&

Wires are made out of Plates + Wire Cutter or simple shears.

Are you lazy and busy? Then try the "Automatic Lubricator".
You can place this little machine to the lubricant input of machines and they will drain it automatically into the machine.

Even in difficult places energy is possible with a Portable Generator.

It is directly connectible with a Wire and keeps its inventory, if you break it down.
This book is the knowledge monster.

Next you need a "cauldron" (Petal Apothecary).

Your main instrument to create seeds and other Botania items.

The "Mana Pool" is a storage block for your mana.
Address a mana spreader to the pool, so that it can send and store it inside the pool.

However, the pool can be used to convert items, too. Look inside your Lexica Botania about what's all possible.

(Or use JEI)
To handle Mana, you need this wand.

The way how you can transfer mana, is with this spreader.
You have to bind flowers to the spreader. (shift + right click with your Wand)

Also, your wand shows details about the mana status in your flower and the how mana flows.

Play with your "cauldron" and create your first useful flower.

Throw the materials into the cauldron, complete your recipe with a Seed.

To get further, you need more flowers.
You already got one as present, but this is not enough.

With the power of the Pure Daisy, you can convert Stone and Logs into their Botania counterparts.
Important: This is §lnot§r a crafting recipe, it's an in-world transmutation process.

Construction shape:

 L/S | L/S | L/S

 L/S | P.D. | L/S 

 L/S | L/S | L/S

L = Log, S = Stone, P.D. = Pure Daisy

Earning Mana is simple, this flower requires some heat-producing materials like Coal.

Throw the item on the ground near the flower and after a short time it will start producing mana.

This flower is more simple than the fire flower.

Just place this flower on the same level as your water is.
It will consume the water to produce Mana.
Mana 2go: it can charge mana items in your inventory.
Improve your inventory crafting with this practical item.
You can see much more details with this.

It lives under the surface and is discoverable with a hoe.

Till some Grass / Dirt to obtain some Worms. It will make the earth great again.
The Worm need seeds, build a little farm.
A fancy Kitchens Knife; some good recipes are preparable with it.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Favourite food of the French people.
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Was the reward good? Yes? Good, then create more.^^

It's planted, and maybe already harvested? But wait, without a Cup its really wasteful.

Craft it first!
Like everywhere you need materials, this time you can earn them from the Waterstrainer and/or Sieves.

Your first machine is the Atomic Reconstructor.
It's powerfull.

Info: you can control the Reconstructor with a Redstone Torch and active it with a Button.

You can generate energy via Coal, build a Coal Generator. 

(Since AA v142, the Coal Gen. is faster)

Upgrade your Reconstructor with lenses:
- Lens of the Miner
- Lens of Disenchanting
- Lens of the killer
- Lens of Certain Death
- Lens of Detonation
- Lens of Color
To go on, you need the Wrench from Actually Additions.

A wonderful way to transport fluids, energy and items is via W-LAN.

Nothing (except the range) can stop the connection. So you can send it through walls.

A few more items you will need. 

Craft a Chest and a Hopper and if you want to sort, you also need a little Filter.

Solar power is a regenerative way to generate energy.

Mother Nature will be happy about it. ;:=)
Canola Oil is burnable in the Oil Generator.

Another way to generate power:
This time with Canola.

To charge items, the Empowerer is your device.

It is a bit complex, so better read the page in the book.

Your Cup needs to be filled up in the Coffee Machine.
Take some energy and a Bucket of Water and heat up the machine!

All is done, activate the machine and wait a little moment.

Info: you can add some effects to it.

With energy and this machine, you can start to transform.

Throw the items in front of the machine (the green side) and press the button.
(be attentive, the machine needs a lot of energy)

Fluid Pipes work identically to the Item Pipes.



§7§oAccording to the developer, a critical distortion of the space-time continuum would only occur during operation of about 300,000 of such tubes, but this has never been experimentally confirmed.
Auto-fishing in very simple, place this block above water and above the Net, a Chest. (or other container blocks)
To recycle the fertilizer overflow that you get when maintaining fields, use the compost to get good fertilizer back.

Excellent pipes to transfer items between 2 points.

5 kinds of pipes are available (all of them have 1 "slot" internal inventory):
- §4Extraction Pipe, §bextract items/fluids out of inventories
§r- §2Injection Pipe, §binsert items/fluids into inventories
§r- §5Source Pipe /Destination Pipe, §r§bdon't interact with inventories themselves but machines can interact with them.
- §7§8Transport Pipes, §bto fill the spacial gap between the other pipes§r

§nInfo:§r You can merge resource flows along pipes, but splitting them is not that simple.
So the best way to deliver multiple targets is to connect Injection Pipes in §9series§r.

Tanks with some special features:
- keeps fluid content when dismantling
- transfers to lower placed tanks
- can be used to fill and empty buckets and other containers.

You ever wanted a §nperfect§r chest with exactly 4 slots and a stack limit of 6 ?
Probably not, but still the Item Buffer is the perfect storage for items in automation setups!

I could explain the buffer, but with the §o"I"§r in the inventory you can find all the detailed information.

Info: the Item Buffers are better for server performance, in contrast to vanilla chests.

Auto-Crafting devices come in all sorts of types, however this one works a little bit different than most conventional ones. (Maybe better)

Info: more details can you find in the §o"§9I§r§o"§r.

Resource buffering in pipes is "problematic". Therefore we ignore it and build the universal pipes. =)
They teleport the items instantly between 2 points.

If you use them clever, then you can have independent lines within the same pipe structure.
Info: "Master connections" (Extraction/Injection) can only interact with "slave connections"(Source/Destination).

The Item Filter can be used for Item Pipes, they have many options.

Rightclick in air to open the config screen and a simple rightclick on the pipe to install.

The Fluid Filter can be used for Fluid Pipes, they have many options.

Rightclick in air to open the config screen and a simple rightclick on the pipe to install.

Auto crafting is good.

-> Portable auto crafting is better.
Wireless Access Terminal for all blocks that have an inventory.

These machines can create lakes or drain them empty.
But be warned: They can flood your basement if you are not careful enough.

The logistically easiest way to operate them, is with a sufficiently large liquid tank, put directly into the machines interface.

To void superfluous items, we need a trash can.
Inductive Logistics has an Overflow Trash, this helps you to prevent lag from items spilling all over the place. :)

Tanks with some special features:
- keeps fluid content when dismantling
- transfers to lower placed tanks
- can be used to fill and empty buckets and other containers.

But, they are also available in bigger versions.
And you should build the §9§lbiggest§r§r one of course. :^)

Item-Droppers or Collectors are often inflexible in their usability.
The Dropped-Item Interface however is just a virtual inventory that represents all items laying around inside a specific area.

Its difficult to interact with something like Chest Minecarts. Hoppers are okay, but it could work better.

I could explain the machine, but with the §o"I"§r in the inventory you can find the detailed informations.

Info: be careful with this device, it works with player inventories, too. :)

The Buffer sizes are variable, more slots and higher stack limits.

So, build the biggest!

Info: the Item Buffers are better for server performance, in contrast to vanilla chests.

The start to the success.

This book contains §call§f important machine blue prints.

The "Key" to the success.

Right click the machines to form it.

All in one and 1 item for everything!

Right click the item, to open the menu.

To place the rail, you need:
- Rail casting in the right size
- Treated Wood
A fancy Train for the start.
Trains are there to attract wagons.
Refined Storage.

§1AE 2§r - an old friend.

But now with integrated Fluid Systems.
Main place to store your HDDs.

Who knows the reference ? ^^

Nevermind, the Grid is your central place to interact with the system.
Main place to store your HDDs.
The Terminal is your central place to interact with the system.
Cables are the stable way, to connect everything.

It's more complex, in AE2. ^^

§nInfo:§r Glass Cables have a maximum of 8 channels.

Same as the Glass Cables, but now with visualizations.

§nInfo:§r Smart Cables have a maximum of 8 channels.

Same as the Smart Cables, but bigger and with more channels.

§nInfo:§r Dense Cables have a maximum of 32 channels.

We don't know the in-game speed, but in real life, the SSD is faster.

§nInfo:§r you don't need to start with the 64k cell right now.

We don't know the in-game speed, but in real life, the SSD is faster.

§nInfo:§r you don't need to start with the 64k cell right now.
Interfaces are awesome, they are the key to connect external things.
Interfaces are awesome, they are the key to connect external things.

Import Bus = Import into the system.

Export Bus = Export from the system.

Import Bus = Import into the system.

Export Bus = Export from the system.
Refined Storage need it.
Uncovered Cables look good, but with Covers they look better.
Both are the same, only the look is different. (and the cost)
Uncovered Cables look good, but with Facades they look better.
A Controller with max. 8 channels and less energy consumption.

§nCraft -> Place -> Adjust -> Click.§r

The "Crafter" is your machine in Refined Storage.

§nInfo:§r you don't need to start with the 64k cell right now.

The Information Screen from RFTools Power is powerful.

You can connect it on §dEVERY§r Energy Cell. (okay, it §oshould§o§r)

§nCraft -> Place -> Adjust -> Click.§r

The "Molecular Assembler" is your machine in Applied Energistics 2.

§nInfo:§r you don't need to start with the 64k cell right now.

Variant "Low" is the first, it stores a lot of §cRedstone Flux.§r

§nInfo:§r 100.000 RF per "Low - Powercell" block.

Variant "Medium" is the second, it stores MORE §cRedstone Flux.§r

§nInfo:§r 2.500.000 RF per "Medium - Powercell" block.

Variant "High" is the third, it stores the MOST §cRedstone Flux.§r 

§n§r§nInfo:§r 12.500.000 RF per "High - Powercell" block.

The main resource for the Backpack.

§nDon't forget:§r They are colorable.

Increase the capacity.

T1 size -> 3x9 Slots.

Increase the capacity.

T2 size -> 4x9 Slots.

Increase the capacity.

T3 size -> 5x9 Slots.

Increase the capacity.

T4 size -> 6x9 Slots.

Increase the capacity.

T5 size -> 7x9 Slots.

Link your private Ender Chest.

Size of the Ender Backpack -> 3x9 Slots.

Here you learn, how to work efficiently.

The "Metallurgic Infuser" is so to say an "Alloy Smelter", it combines a material with some other.

You can increase your yield with the "Enrichment Chamber", so stop wasting resources.

Create the following Items:
- §7Compressed Carbon
§r- §bCompressed Diamond
§r- §5Compressed Obsidian

Brine is a liquid and its not easy to produce.
You need a tower, a kind of "brewing tower".

§bWater§f + §cEnergy§f = §eBrine§f

The tower is a 5x5x(x) big multi-block structure, with minimum:

- 1 Controller
- 2 Valves
- + some blocks.

The Wind Generator generates Energy.

On a higher place, he'll generate more.
Like the charging station from IC2, simply stand on this Charge Pad to charge all your inventory containing energy items/tools.

The ultimate ore processing.

Its a high technical construction, I can't explain it here, so please Google it.

=)

These water pumps are good for the Brine production.

The can hold upgrades, are efficient and fast.

our Journey Map can teleport you around, but we disabled it. :) (minimum on our Server)

Consequently we need other teleport items, like the "Portable Teleporter".

§nInfo:§r The frames are for a "Portal", I hope. ^^
These Light spots are little and bright, they might be a good alternative to Torches.

This is your journey, a §9spiritual§r journey.

You learn about new plants and grow together with them, to USE their power!

New experience and spells to defend yourself from the evil enemies.

And all that in the harmony with §2§anature§r.
Are you ready, to go with the mystery of the sound?

You need Light ... and a Furnace.

So, lets start!

To survive, you need food.

To deal with it, you can keep animals, however they need to be maintained.

Now we have light and a good Furnace.

But we need other ores and resources.

With this, we start §1Now§r.
Just Reliquary. =D

The ways in which you can collect your resources is diverse, default with meshes and interesting with §2flowers§r.
Here you can explore how.
Industrial revolution in a Game.
A strong weapon, these harmless§o§o §6§oplants§r§r.
Great stuff combined into one mod.

Harmless and friendly, the transport- and storage system from Inductive Logistics.

@CD4017BE is our master.
A realistic Train mod, 200% fun and a heart for model railroad lovers.
Nothing to say here. ^^

"That's a lot of damage" - not this time !

This is: "a lot of energy".
Some stuff from earlier ages return.
High Tech, in a different version.
